      • save

        public void save(java.io.File xmlfile)
          throws java.io.IOException
        Description copied from interface: View
        Save the view without materializing the data. That is: An xml file will be created that stores all meta information. At runtime, when you want to use values in this view, this information is sufficient to find these values in the views or underlying datasets that this view consists of.
        Specified by:
        save in interface View
        Throws:

      • saveMaterialized

        public View saveMaterialized(java.io.File xmlfile,
                    java.io.File datafile,
                    FileFormat format)
                      throws java.io.IOException
        Description copied from interface: View
        Save the view materialized. That means, that all values that you can see in this view will be written to a file that is specified by datafile and is of format specified by fileformat. An xml file is created that stores a view that points directly to this datafile. This is mainly for speed reasons, as at some point, when a view consists of a very large tree, lots of data have to be read, filtered, merged and so on.
        Specified by:
        saveMaterialized in interface View
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
